The paper deals with the performance analysis of a non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) network in finite blocklength regime, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on achieving low latency and high reliability, which are important aspects of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses the effective capacity (EC) framework, which is a tool commonly used in the analysis of communication systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper considers transmissions over Rayleigh fading channels, which is a topic related to wireless communication (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with multiuser NOMA networks, which is a topic related to communication networks (cs.COM).
